ùThe Sorbus tree in the North side of the garden
was planted in memory of
Sir Terence Rattigan, CBE (1911-1977)
by David Suchet CBE
on 22nd May 2012"ø
ÿIn loving memory of Sabine Vogler,
Confidante and love of my life,
Who walked through this park often
On her way elsewhere
in London with me. Ôê×+3."ø
ÿHAROLD ARTHUR DUDMAN:
MARCH 5TH 1923 - JUNE 6TH 2009
FREEMAN OF THE CITY OF LONDON,
WANDSMAN OF
ST. PAUL'S CATHEDRAL

[Second inscription added 2019]
ALSO HIS BELOVED WIFE
OF 58 YEARS
EDITH IRENE (LESLEY) DUDMAN
JANUARY 26TH 1926 - MARCH 24TH 2019
REUNITED FOR ETERNITY"í
×Dedicated to the memory of
Rene Tkacik
who lost his life working in the Crossrail tunnels
on the 7th of March 2014
from his family, friends and colleagues"ó
ƒTo the very dear memory of
Hannelore Nath "Anne"
who loved London and the changing of
the seasons in its beautiful parks and squares
Danzig 1932    London 2009"Ñ
